<![CDATA[
Authoring Tool Accessibility Guidelines (ATAG) 2.0 Candidate Recommendation (CR) has been updated with simplified exit criteria to bring it more in line with common W3C practices for CR exit criteria. There are no substantive changes to ATAG 2.0 itself, only to the CR exit criteria. Implementing ATAG 2.0 is also updated to keep cross-linking between [&#8230;]<img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4739%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Datag-2-0-cr-updated-with-simplified-exit-criteria&amp;action_name=ATAG+2.0+CR+updated+with+simplified+exit+criteria&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" />
